[30;1m61 | [0m[35m# The ground slope itself is always positive, but the component of the slope[0m
[30;1m62 | [0m[35m# perpendicular to the tracker axes can be positive or negative. The convention[0m
[30;1m63 | [0m[35m# for the cross-axis slope angle follows the right-hand rule: align[0m
[30;1m64 | [0m[35m# the right-hand thumb along the tracker axis in the direction of the axis[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35m# azimuth and the fingers curl towards positive angles. So in this example,[0m

[30;1m7 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m# %%[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35m# Tracker systems use backtracking to avoid row-to-row shading when the[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35m# sun is low in the sky. The backtracking strategy orients the modules exactly[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35m# on the boundary between shaded and unshaded so that the modules are oriented[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m# as much towards the sun as possible while still remaining unshaded.[0m

   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
